        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-15T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-15T01:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.248/12–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-15T14:00:00+08:00">December 15, 1948—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 15—9:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2779. Re Deptel 2160, December 12, repeated Nanking 1810. CAF now moving out some
                    materials on Chinese ships arranged by CAF direct. Everett Steamship Co.
                    offering provide possible 7 vessels various flags within next 3 weeks.</p>
                <p>Initiative now rests with CAF who state their present needs taken care of. 60,000
                    tons remain to move but CAF do not want to move entire amount immediately as
                    would deplete stocks now being used Shanghai.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2779, repeated Nanking 2085.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
